         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">he who was Śilpavān is [now] to be known as Aniruddha. He who was Prajñavān, is now to be known as Śāriputra.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a1 #a2 #a3 #a4 #a5 #a6 #b1 #b2 #b3 #b4 #b5 #b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:sieg1944"/><citedRange>20</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>18, 287</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>75</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">He who at that time was Puṇyavān, I was he. Also at that time by the power of virtue I surpassed all other beings,</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2 #a3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>190</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1958a"/><citedRange>142</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>72</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">and without effort reached royal dignity. Even now, by the power of virtue I sit upon the diamond throne,</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3 #a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>169</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1976"/><citedRange>228</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3 #a4 #a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1991"/><citedRange>19</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3ff"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1969"/><citedRange>264</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>99</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1991"/><citedRange>21</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">I have [also], without effort, defeated the army of the god Māra [consisting] of 36 times 10 million family members, and the dignity of the king of the world,</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">the unsurpassable, perfect Buddhahood, ruling all dharmas, I have reached. || In the H.-tune: || through virtue</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5 #a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1954"/><citedRange>740</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(beauty) is fine to look at; through virtue the craft of the beings is lovely to look at; through the foundation of virtue, unch(ecked shines)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>139</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>99</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(wis)dom; through the power of virtue, energy does not weaken. [1.] Through virtue the sun defeats the moon in the airspace;</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Durch die Kraft der Tugendhaftigkeit lässt die Energie nicht nach.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Through the power of virtuousness, the energy does not weaken.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>103</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1 #b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1969"/><citedRange>251</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Durch die Tugendhaftigkeit besiegt die Sonne den Mond im Luftraum, durch die Tugendhaftigkeit übertrifft der Mond die Sterne [und] Planeten.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Through virtue the sun defeats the moon in the airspace, through virtue the moon surpasses the stars [and] planets.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>511</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>354</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">by merits the moon surpasses the stars and the planets; he who possesses virtue, this one owns the goods of happiness; through virtue</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2 #b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>111f</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Durch die Tugendhaftigkeit wird man [wtl. ist man fähig] zu dem mit Verehrung behandelten Buddha.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Through virtuousness one can become a Buddha, treated with reverence. </seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>111-2</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>9</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1952"/><citedRange>20</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1958"/><citedRange>292</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1981"/><citedRange>492</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">one becomes the venerated Buddha. 2. Therefore the veneration of the Buddha shall ever be carried out by the wise one;</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1952"/><citedRange>19</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">incessantly the energetic ones shall strive to carry out veneration of the Buddha; at the Buddha, the master, the skilled one shall direct veneration;</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>295</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1952"/><citedRange>20</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1981"/><citedRange>495</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">the handsome one should not tire of homages to the Buddha. 3. In this way wisdom without virtue does not shine, or</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5 #b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1958a"/><citedRange>161</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>262</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">rather, only together they are especially bright. Therefore they are themselves called Sambhāras. These two Sambhāras’ (six)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6 "><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>312</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>337</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6 txt:m-a18#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>207</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">In den sechs Pāramitās [vollkommenen Tugenden] d[ies] er zwei Saṃbhāras aber hat sich der Buddha, der Meister, in drei Asaṃkhyeyas [und] hundert Kalpas geübt.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">In the six pāramitās [perfect virtues] of the[se] two saṃbhāras, however, the Buddha, the master, exercised himself in three asaṃkhyeyas [and] a hundred kalpas.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>337</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
